race.comment: BUCKINGHAM PALACE (3) is long overdue for a maiden win. Has placed 4/6 and both runs this time in, both in far richer company. Back to the provincials and has a bit on these on best, if Holder can weave some magic from the wide draw. TIDDY WIDDY (12) is better than recent form and looks ideally placed. Placed three back at this level then the last two have been in richer company. Has pace and will take running down. ROYOLO (10) is a four-year-old mare on debut for the Doudle team. By Royal Meeting from Yolo Girl. Trialling in good style and looks forward enough. Bold showing expected. MISS LIL (7) resumes from a long spell. Will give a start at this trip but find the line hard.
